SEC. 12. All applicants for registration as master plumber shall be required to pass an examination as hereinafter provided.

Persons applying for admission to the examination as herein provided, shall, prior to the date of the examination, establish to the satisfaction of the Board of Examiners, that he:

Is at least twenty-one years of age;

Is a citizen of the Philippines;

Is of good moral character;

Is at least a high school graduate;

Has at least five years experience in actual plumbing work under the supervision of a registered master plumber.

SEC. 13. Applicants for registration as master plumbers shall be examined in the following subjects:

Plumbing arithmetic, ten per cent;

Plumbing Code, ten per cent;

Sanitation, plumbing design and installation, forty per cent;

Practical problems, twenty per cent;

Oral practical problems and experience, twenty per cent.

SEC. 14. The Board shall, within one hundred and twenty days after the date of completion of the examination, report the rating obtained by each candidate to the Commissioner of Civil Service, who shall submit such ratings to the president of the Philippines.
